Let $u = 1/x$, so that $\mathrm{d}x = -\frac{\mathrm{d}u}{u^2}$ and the limits swap to give
\[
\int_0^\infty \frac{\mathrm{d}x}{(1+x^2)(1+x^a)}
=\int_\infty^0 \frac{-\mathrm{d}u/u^2}{\left(1+\frac{1}{u^2}\right)\left(1+\frac{1}{u^a}\right)}
=\int_0^\infty \frac{u^{a}\,\mathrm{d}u}{(1+u^2)(1+u^a)}.
\]
